## ⚠️ Issues Found

### 1. Dead Code — Old flows never called
**Lines 923-1376**: [_do_toplist_style()](file:///f:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/ui/rewrite_style_tab.py#923-1100) and [_do_narrative_style()](file:///f:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/ui/rewrite_style_tab.py#1103-1361) are **never called** by the dispatcher. They are dead code from the old 3-mode system.

> **Impact**: No functional impact, but bloats the file by ~450 lines.
> **Recommendation**: Remove both functions to clean up.

---

### 2. Comment outdated (minor)
**Line 109**: Comment says `"# Framework selector (only visible for Renew mode)"` but Renew mode no longer exists. Both modes now show framework.

> **Impact**: Cosmetic only.
> **Recommendation**: Update comment.

---

### 3. Docstring outdated (minor)
**Lines 1-4**: Module docstring mentions `"Two modes: Top/List (parallel) and Narrative (sequential)"` — this describes the OLD system.

> **Impact**: Cosmetic only.
> **Recommendation**: Update to describe `Top/List Review` and `Narrative` pipelines.

---

### 4. [_show_style_popup](file:///f:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/ui/rewrite_style_tab.py#325-328) → potential infinite loop risk
**Line 325-326**: [_show_style_popup](file:///f:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/ui/rewrite_style_tab.py#325-328) calls [_refresh_style_dropdown()](file:///f:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/ui/rewrite_style_tab.py#284-324) which reads JSON files from disk. If the style combo's `currentTextChanged` signal fires during this refresh (despite `blockSignals`), it would call [_on_mode_changed](file:///f:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/ui/rewrite_style_tab.py#787-834) again.

> **Impact**: Currently **mitigated** by `blockSignals(True)` in [_refresh_style_dropdown](file:///f:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/ui/rewrite_style_tab.py#284-324). Safe, but fragile.
> **Recommendation**: No action needed, but be aware.

---

### 5. [_save_status_safe](file:///f:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/ui/rewrite_style_tab.py#728-738) used in review flow but definition not verified
**Line 2146**: `self._save_status_safe(group_path)` is called during review chapter writing. If this method doesn't exist or has issues, it will crash during the review pipeline.

> **Impact**: Could crash during review if function is missing or broken.
> **Recommendation**: Verify this function exists and works.

---

### 6. [chapter_range_rule](file:///f:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/ui/rewrite_style_tab.py#361-372) not passed into [create_review_outline](file:///f:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/rewriter.py#1740-1811)
**Line 2031**: [create_review_outline()](file:///f:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/rewriter.py#1740-1811) is called without the chapter range rule from Ch min/max spinboxes. The outline AI won't know how many chapters the user wants.

> **Impact**: **Functional** — AI may generate any number of chapters regardless of Ch settings.
> **Recommendation**: Pass `chapter_range_rule=self._get_chapter_range_rule()` to [create_review_outline](file:///f:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/rewriter.py#1740-1811).

---

